But nowadays women want brand names and logos. I don’t like logos. I don’t like showing a woman a dress and telling them it’s a Prada or an Oscar. 'Whose is it?’ they’ll ask automatically, especially the oldest, biggest, I-can’t-even-tell-you-who-they-are customers. The whole 'what’s my best friend wearing?’ thing is stronger than it has ever been. Women are so competitive at the moment, especially in their thirties and forties.
